news.title: Indonesia's Waskita, Wijaya Karya make headway in restructuring talks
news.para: Waskita CEO Muhammad Hanugroho told a parliamentary hearing, his company's total debt as of the end of 2023 was 41.2 trillion rupiah ($2.62 billion), 26.3 trillion of which were bank loans.

news.title: Builder’s error in allotting flat will not impact tax benefit claim: ITAT
news.para: Section 54 of the I-T Act provides that any long term capital gain arising to an individual on sale of a residential property shall be exempt to the extent that such capital gain is invested in the purchase of another residential property within one year before or two years after such sale.

news.title: Single-family housing starts, permits in USA near two year high in February
news.para: Despite the hurdle created for many first-time buyers by higher mortgage rates, builders are cutting prices and offering other incentives to increase sales.

news.title: Lucknow: 24 allottees get their property registered at LDA’s special camp
news.para: The camp aims to provide a hassle-free registration process for various LDA residential and commercial properties. During the day, documents for registration of 48 properties were prepared.

news.title: Unified rules to aid high-rise boom in 23 merged localities of Pune
news.para: Developers and landowners are likely to benefit from provisions such as relaxations in the side margins. This will lead to an increase in high-rise buildings in the added areas, mostly in the city’s fringes.

news.title: Indore administration to inspect fire safety measures in buildings taller than G+3
news.para: “In order to prevent fire accidents in the district, security measures will be strengthened. New vehicles will be purchased for firefighting arrangements and improvements will be made in operations,” said collector Asheesh Singh.

news.title: HC seeks Uttar Pradesh govt's reply on plea challenging recent ordinance on Nazul land policy
news.para: The ordinance prescribes that there will be no freehold of such land and no extension of lease after the lease period ends. This move is intended to ensure that Nazul lands, once the lease period expires, are vested in the State.

news.title: Madras HC appoints committee to find accommodations for owners of Jain’s Westminster apartments
news.para: “The committee will have retired judges K N Basha and K Kannan to supervise the evacuation of the occupants and provide alternative accommodation,” a division bench of justice S S Sundar and justice N Senthilkumar said on Tuesday.

news.title: Water crisis hits construction in Belagavi
news.para: Local administration has urged the public to use water judiciously, given the fast-depleting water levels in the reservoirs. Even the daily scheduled water supply has been delayed.

news.title: Trichy corporation increases net tax collection to 85% by targeting top defaulters
news.para: This year, tax defaulters delaying payments varying between Rs 1 lakh and Rs 2 lakh per property were primarily focussed, resulting in collection of around Rs 18 crore in the last two months.

news.title: Over 1,300 homes in cantonment area likely to come under Sambhajinagar civic body
news.para: The possible change in the governing authority of these dwellings is taking place in the wake of the proposed merger of the civil areas of Cantonment into the local civic body.

news.title: Gujarat: Advocates can't be prosecuted for sale deed fraud
news.para: The earlier notification, issued on March 7, stated that in instances where property deeds were found to be fraudulent, the two parties involved in the sale deed as well as the advocate who prepared the deed were liable for prosecution.

news.title: Kolkata civic body serves notices to promoters of six illegal buildings
news.para: Among these buildings in Azhar Molla Bagan, one is tilting and needs to be razed to prevent another tragedy, said a KMC buildings department official. They are looking for three other buildings in the vicinity that have tilted as well.

news.title: SC stays Delhi HC order asking Unitech's founder to surrender immediately
news.para: Chandra was arrested by the Enforcement Directorate (ED) in October 2021 in connection with a money laundering probe against the real estate group and its promoters.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government cracks down on illegal villas on East Coast Road
news.para: Residents of Thazhuthala Kuppam village had filed a case, seeking directions from the tribunal to the govt to demolish all ‘illegal’ constructions in neighbouring Paramankeni and Mudaliarkuppam.

news.title: Delhi development body gets tepid response to plan for unauthorised colonies
news.para: 4.75 lakh residents in unauthorized colonies applied for ownership rights under PM Uday Yojana. Hurdles like high fees and limited benefits faced. Officials aim to simplify processes and enhance infrastructure for over 1,700 colonies.

news.title: UltraTech Cement gets CCI's nod to acquire Kesoram Cement
news.para: The proposed combination relates to the acquisition of the grey cement business of Kesoram Industries Limited by UltraTech Cement Ltd pursuant to a composite scheme of arrangement dated November 30, 2023, according to a release.

news.title: Haryana RERA cancels registrations of five housing projects of Mahira Infratech
news.para: The Authority took the step after the builder failed to comply with the provisions of the RERA Act and complete construction of all five affordable housing projects across various sectors in Gurugram, the official added.

news.title: MahaRERA proposes three separate bank accounts for better monitoring of projects
news.para: The separate accounts have been proposed to ensure financial discipline and better monitoring of the money received from the allottees.

news.title: China stocks fall by 0.7% over deepening property crisis
news.para: ​​China's Shanghai Composite Index and the blue-chip CSI300 Index both lost 0.7% at market close, Hong Kong's benchmark Hang Seng and the Hang Seng China Enterprises Index fell 1.2% each.
